keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000015#     2#          905#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> and <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 15.2-908"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 15.2-908">15.2-908<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000015#     2#          908#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> or city charter relating to the external maintenance of property or local zoning ordinances relating to motor vehicles or trailers as defined in <citation type="statute" normalizedCite="VACODE 46.2-100"><content><span normalizedCite="Va. Code Ann. § 46.2-100">§ 46.2-100<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#7159#349#000046#     2#          100#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation> may utilize supervised, trained and qualified volunteers to issue notices of noncompliance with such ordinances. Such volunteers shall have any and all immunity provided to an employee of the locality doing an identical job.</p></bodyText><history><historyGroup groupType="history-citation"><historyItem><bodyText><p>Acts <citation normalizedCite="2000 VA CH 673"><content><span normalizedCite="2000 Va. Ch. 673">2000, c. 673<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2000#000673#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2002 VA CH 31"><content><span normalizedCite="2002 Va. Ch. 31">2002, cc. 31<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2002#000031#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>, <citation normalizedCite="2002 VA CH 451"><content><span normalizedCite="2002 Va. Ch. 451">451<locator><locatorKey><keyName name="citeReference"/><keyValue value="#1834#131#2002#000451#"/></locatorKey></locator></span></content></citation>; <citation normalizedCite="2005 VA CH 265"><content><span normalizedCite="2005 